Why is your `CrudRepository` defined as `CrudRepository&lt;UserModel, String&gt;`? 

It should be `CrudRepository&lt;UserModel, Long&gt;` because the `id` of your `UserModel` entity is of type `Long`.

Also, in the query you&#39;ve presented:

&gt;  `@Transactional
@Modifying(clearAutomatically = true)
@Query(&quot;UPDATE user u SET u.internalId=:internalId WHERE u.id=:id&quot;)
void markEntryAsRead(@Param(&quot;id&quot;) String id, @Param(&quot;internalId&quot;) String   internalId);`

you pass `id` parameter as `String`, but in should be `int`, because in your entity you have `private int id;` Same with `internalId`.

**So**

 try to define your `CrudRepository` as `CrudRepository&lt;UserModel, Long&gt;`, and use not `User`, but `UserModel` in your Queries, e.g.:

